{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YFRwqCnhjMnqyXRaNMpsbV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three jobs have completed. Here's the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Results\n\n### Bugs Diagnosed and Fixed\n\nThe committed YAML files had three bugs preventing correct job execution:\n\n1. **`skew-job.yaml`**: `serviceAccountName: spark-wrong` — non-existent service account would block pod scheduling. Fixed to `spark`.\n2. **All three job YAMLs**: The `spark-submit` command ran `SparkPi` (a trivial example) instead of the actual data-skew analysis scripts. Fixed to decode and run the correct Python scripts via `base64 -d`.\n\n### Performance Comparison\n\n| Strategy | Elapsed | Optimization | Benefit |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Baseline** | 17.19s | None | skewed shuffle join (straggler risk) |\n| **Broadcast Join** | 7.98s | Broadcast small `products` table | No shuffle, no skew — **2.15× faster** |\n| **AQE** | 8.14s | Auto-splits hot partitions at runtime | Auto skew-join handling — **2.11× faster** |\n\n### Data Skew Observed\n- `skew_ratio = 44x` (max partition: 11,579 rows vs min: 263 rows) — confirming severe skew around the hot `product_id` values 1–5\n\n### Why It Works\n- **Broadcast join**: eliminates the shuffle entirely — the small `products` table (100 rows) is broadcast to every executor, so skewed `product_id` partitions never need to send data across the network.\n- **AQE**: detects skewed partitions at runtime and automatically splits them, distributing the straggler work across multiple tasks.\n\nBoth optimization strategies delivered ~2.1× speedup over the unoptimized baseline, with identical correct query results across all three runs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":368,"cache_read_input_tokens":56217,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":368},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5986c19-7fa9-4c8d-b4b7-c21394aae23d","uuid":"ce1905ec-b3c0-4378-8156-6f1b2f7a30d3","request_id":"req_011CbyrkuJ5w5aKHUrtdf1kU"}
